    <section id="home">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Home</h2>
      <img src="profile.jpg" alt="Profile Photo" class="w-32 h-32 object-cover rounded-full mb-4">
      <p>Dr Fatma Canan Durgungoz is a Research Fellow at the University of Bath, UK. She holds a PhD in Special Education from the University of Nottingham, a Master’s degree from Nottingham Trent University, and a BA in Child Development from Hacettepe University.</p>
      <p>Her research interests include developmental language disorder (DLD), special educational needs (SEN), inclusive technologies, and parental interventions. She co-leads the British Council-funded EDAR project which supports academics affected by the 6th February earthquake in Turkey.</p>
    </section>

